A member of the South African National Defence Force (SANDF) based in the eastern Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) tried to kill himself after he allegedly shot his girlfriend, also a member of the SANDF based in the DRC, the SANDF said on Saturday. His alleged girlfriend died on arrival at theÂ hospital in Goma after the shooting at about 8.45pm on Friday. The man was in a critical condition in hospital in Goma. The motive behind the shooting was not yet known, Brigadier-General Mafi Mgobozi said. The name of the deceased would be released once the next-of-kin had been formally informed. Defence and Military Veterans Minister Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula, Defence Secretary Sam Gulube, and SANDF chief Lieutenant-General Solly Shoke expressed their heartfelt condolences to the family, friends and loved ones of the deceased member, Mgobozi said. African News Agency